%\begin{abstract}
\begin{center}
{\LARGE Abstract}
\end{center}
Denial of service attack (DoS) is critical threat to the internet and causes serious impact on the computing systems such as database server, web server, cloud computing server etc. DoS attack stops legitimate user from accessing online services. Therefore effective detection of DoS attack is necessary to increase the efficiency of server. This present Multivariate correlation analysis (MCA) for network traffic characterization overcomes the problem of DoS attack. MCA uses triangle area technique for extracting correlations between observed network traffic. Triangle area based technique is proposed to speed up the MCA process. Then SVM (Support Vector Machine) based classification technique used for attack classification using the triangle area based multivariate correlation information. The normalization method presented to increase the detection rate of DoS attack.

%\end{abstract}

