\section{Algorithm}

\begin{enumerate}

\item First taking kddcup99 dataset as input.
\item selection of features.
\item Normalize features of dataset by min-max normalization(described in methodology chapter equation{(1)}).
\item Determine triangular area among network features using  $TA_{j,k}^{i}=\frac{\left(\mid f_j^i\mid\times \mid f_k^i\mid\right)  }{2}$
     where j and k are two distinct features of $ i^{th} $ m-dimentional traffic record
\item Indexing All triangle areas with respect to their indexes i.e TAM matrix.
\item Using only lower triangular matrix for generating covariance \& mahalnobis distance because TAM is symmetric matrix.
\item Generating the covariance matrix and mahalnobis distance (using equations{(5),(6)\& (7)} from methodology chapter).
\item Generate SMO SVM model.
\item Testing dataset file selection
\item classification of dos attack type record from normal records using support vector machine(SVM) (described in section 7.3).

\end{enumerate}

