\chapter{Results and Evaluation}

\textbf{Evaluation measures:}\\
During the evaluation, some instances of the 10 percent labeled data of KDD Cup 99 dataset is used, where three types of legitimate traffic i.e
TCP,UDP and ICMP traffic and six types of DoS attacks i.e Teardrop,Smurf,Pod,Neptune,Land and Back attacks are available.\\
\\
To estimate the performance of the system,three important formulae are used i.e accuracy,false positive rate and detection rate.
 To estimate these formulae we need false negative (FN), True positive (TP), false positive (FP), True negative (TN) rate measures.
  These are described below: \\
\\
TP- Attack occurs and alarm generates.\\
TN- No attack occurs and no alarm generates.\\
FP- No attack occurs but alarm generates.\\
FN- Attack occurs but alarm not generates.\\

The accuracy,detection rate and false positive rate is determined using formulae described below[34][35].\\

Accuracy = $\frac{tp+tn}{tp+fp+tn+fn}\times100$
\\

Detection Rate(DR) = $\frac{tp}{tp+tn}\times100$
\\

False Positive Rate(FPR) = $\frac{fp}{fp+tn}\times100$
\\




Accuracy is determined for 100,200,300,400,500 instances of kddcup99 dataset and also for five sets of
different 100 instances of the kddcup99 dataset for training.we used 123 instance testing dataset for evaluation.\\

The comparative accuracy graph of 100,200,300,400,500 instances of dataset is shown in fig. 10.3 And Table 10.1 describes accuracy results
of SVM, MLP, zeroR for 100,200,300,400,500 instances of kddcup99 dataset.

