%%%%%%%%%%  CHAPTER 8 %%%%%%%%%%
\chapter{Conclusion}
%
The triangle area technique extracts correlations between two distinct features within traffic records.
 Therefore proposed system uses triangle area based multivariate correlation technique.
  Also it uses support vector machine classifier which classifies attacks from legitimate network traffic.
  By using the triangle area technique speed up the process of multivariate correlation analysis.
   This method produces better performance in terms of speed and accuracy. SMO function of support vector machine is used for the classification of attack and normal records.
   It gives more than 95\% accuracy with less time for execution. SVM gives maximum accuracy as compared to MLP and zeroR.
   In future I will use most sophisticated techniques for classification and  use real time data for this purpose.

